title: For Sale:  Confederate p1856 Enfield Cavalry Carbine
postcontent: This is most likely 1 of the 10,000 p1856 Enfield Carbines that were imported for Confederate use during the war. This is not a British used piece, as evident by the lack of WD War Department proofs. The Barnett lockplate has a Crown without the VR, and instead has Tower and another B stamped to the right. The sight leaves are still present, and original to the gun. The barrel has the correct proof marks for Barnett, and the stock still has the correct saddle ring and assembly for mounted use. The ramrod (replaced with a period style that is often seen on the p1856 and p1853 Artillery Carbines) and swivel arm has been broken off, which was probably done by a trooper whom was tired of the awkward movement to return the ramrod. The civilian patch box is most likely post-war, and supports the notion of being a Southern piece. But unlike most of these carbines that became bored out shotguns following the war, this carbine has very strong rifling still! A wonderful piece to have in your Southern Cavalry display or English Import collection!
